summary:
I have supported various financial institutions in their digital transformation. I am a pragmatic, analytical, result driven and engaging professional.

I'm an all-round player, experienced in both strategy development and strategy execution. My heart is with translating the corporate strategy into daily practices, while running the day-to-day business. I lead change with eye and care for the people around me, without compromising on the results that need to be achieved. 

I'm experienced in combining business, technology and regulatory aspects and to translate wishes from different stakeholders. I always dare to ask the right questions, communicate well with all layers of the organisation, and have strong organisational skills. Resulting in a shared view and most important, commitment to the successful delivery. 

Key areas of interest: digital transformation, operating model (re)design, change management.

Feel free to reach out to me via info@fioletconsulting.nl

projects:
[{'title': "President's Programme 2011", 'date': {'start': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2011}, 'end': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2011}}, 'description': 'The President’s Programme is a joint Russian-Dutch initiative dating from 1997, when prime ministers Kok and Chernomyrdin agreed that each year, 50 Russian managers from the private sector would be welcomed in the Netherlands for an educational program. This initiative has been successful throughout the last 15 years, and holds on to its purposes:
Developing and strengthening economic bonds between Russia and the Netherlands;
Cooperation that leads to sharing knowledge about Russian and Dutch society, culture and economy.
The President’s Programme is geared towards prosperous and profitable business relationships. To achieve this, the training is completely focused on preparing economic bonds between Dutch and Russian firms.
But the President’s Programme goes beyond education, in the sense that all participants will be involved in an ‘internship’ in a Dutch firm for a three week period. This is not a standard internship; it is aimed at establishing economic bonds. The Russian manager and their Dutch host company work on finding opportunities for these economic bonds throughout the internship period. In the past, the internships have led to good spin-offs for the Dutch and Russian corporate worlds. Whether in the form of export or import contracts, dealer partnerships, research cooperation and foreign direct investments.
The President’s Programme is facilitated by the Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Josje', 'last_name': 'Fiolet', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Strategy execution & change management'}, {'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Pim', 'last_name': 'van Geest', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Chief Executive Officer at Global Education Futures'}, {'type': 'nonStandardizedContributor', 'first_name': None, 'last_name': None, 'name': 'Henry Robben', 'headline': None}, {'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Gerard', 'last_name': 'Uijtendaal', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Partner at Reanda Netherlands: Transnational Audit | Tax | Advisory | Accountancy'}]}, {'title': 'Shopping Tomorow', 'date': {'start': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}, 'end': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}}, 'description': 'Shopping Tomorrow (formerly Shopping2020) is the platform where retailers continuously jointly explore the development of consumer behavior, technology and the (international) market and come up with concrete actions to improve their own competitive position and that of the Netherlands.
